</p>
<p>These tries to <em>guess</em> the right field type - but it's not always right. <code>speciesCount</code>
should clearly be an integer - set it to that. For a full-list of <em>all</em> the built-in
Doctrine types, check their docs. The most important are <code>string</code>, <code>integer</code>, <code>text</code>,
<code>datetime</code> and <code>float</code>.</p>
<p>Next, head to the bottom of the class to create the getter and setter methods. But
wait! Realize: you might <em>not</em> need getters and setters for <em>every</em> field, so only
add them if you need them. We <em>will</em> need them, so open "Code"-&gt;"Generate" again and
select "Getters and Setters":</p>
